  FoodMenu(
      name: 'Baked Salmon',
      desc: '''Baked salmon is a delicious and nutritious main course that highlights the natural flavors and tender texture of this popular fish. It is a versatile dish that can be prepared using various cooking methods, but baking is a popular choice due to its simplicity and ability to preserve the moisture and delicate taste of the salmon.

To prepare baked salmon, fresh salmon fillets are seasoned with herbs, spices, and a squeeze of lemon juice to enhance their flavors. Common seasonings include salt, pepper, dill, garlic, or a combination of aromatic herbs. The fillets are then placed in a baking dish or on a lined baking sheet, and sometimes brushed with olive oil or melted butter to add a hint of richness and prevent sticking.

The salmon is baked in a preheated oven at a moderate temperature, allowing it to cook gently and evenly. The cooking time depends on the thickness of the fillets and desired doneness, typically ranging from 10 to 15 minutes. It is important to avoid overcooking to maintain the salmon's moistness and prevent it from becoming dry.

Once baked, the salmon emerges with a beautifully flaky texture and a lightly browned exterior. The fish should be opaque and easily flake with a fork when done. Baked salmon can be served as a standalone main course or paired with various sides like roasted vegetables, steamed rice, or a fresh salad. Its rich flavor and Omega-3 fatty acid content make it a nutritious choice that is enjoyed by seafood lovers around the world.''',
